CAPE TOWN, South Africa, August 27, 2018/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            The Minister of Justice and Constitutional Development, Advocate Michael Masutha, will hold a joint media briefing with #FeesMustFall activists on Monday, 27 August 2018. The purpose of the briefing is to give an update on the outcomes of meetings held by Minister Masutha and the student activists who have been protesting at the Union Buildings and Parliament demanding a general amnesty for their fellow comrades who came into conflict with the law as a result of incidents that occurred during the #FeesMustFall campaign protests.





The Media Briefing will be held as follows:

Date:  Monday, 27 August 2018

Time: 10h00

Venue: Tshedimosetso House, 1035 Francis Baard Street, Hatfield, Pretoria,  with a video link to GCIS Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street Parliament, Cape Town.